#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 39"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:0.5"
msgid "39. Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on fine foods"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc39.1, pts-vp-en.2.341, ms2V_824
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six ate fine foods after asking for them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics eat fine foods after asking for them?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.5"
msgid "Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti."
msgstr "Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t want tasty food?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.88, ms2V_825
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.6"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six eat fine foods after asking for them for themselves?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you eat fine foods after asking for them for yourselves?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_826
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.16"
msgid "“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘If a monk asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for himself—that is,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.17"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi."
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, sugar, fish, meat, milk, and curd—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.18"
msgid "Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_827
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:1.19"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc39.2, ms2V_828
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti."
msgstr "At one time a number of monks were sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.2"
msgid "Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks who were looking after them asked,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.342
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.3"
msgid "“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“We hope you’re bearing up; we hope you’re getting better?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.4"
msgid "“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjāma, tena no phāsu hoti;"
msgstr "“Previously we ate fine foods after asking for them, and then we were comfortable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.5"
msgid "idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na viññāpema, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr "But now that this has been prohibited by the Master, we don’t ask because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. And because of that we’re not comfortable.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.6"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.8"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat fine foods after asking for them for himself."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.9a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: seyyathidaṃ → seyyathīdaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_829
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.10"
msgid "“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘If a monk who is not sick asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for himself—that is,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.11"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi."
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, sugar, fish, meat, milk, and curd—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:2.12"
msgid "Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc39.3.1, ms2V_830
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.1"
msgid "Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanānīti "
msgstr "These kinds of fine foods:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="gloss"><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.2"
msgid "sappi nāma"
msgstr "Ghee:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.3"
msgid "gosappi vā ajikāsappi vā mahiṃsasappi vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati tesaṃ sappi."
msgstr "ghee from cows, ghee from goats, ghee from buffaloes, or ghee from whatever animal whose meat is allowable."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_831
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.4"
msgid "Navanītaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Butter:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.5"
msgid "tesaññeva navanītaṃ."
msgstr "butter from those same animals."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_832
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.6"
msgid "Telaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Oil:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.7"
msgid "tilatelaṃ sāsapatelaṃ madhukatelaṃ eraṇḍatelaṃ vasātelaṃ."
msgstr "sesame oil, mustard seed oil, honey tree oil, castor oil, oil from tallow."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_833
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.8"
msgid "Madhu nāma"
msgstr "Honey:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.9"
msgid "makkhikāmadhu."
msgstr "honey from bees."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_834
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.10"
msgid "Phāṇitaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Sugar:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.11"
msgid "ucchumhā nibbattaṃ."
msgstr "from sugar cane."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. VAR: udako → udakacaro (s1-3, pts1, mr)
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_835
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.12"
msgid "Maccho nāma"
msgstr "Fish:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: Here I follow the alternative reading _udakacaro_ found in the PTS version. MS has _udako_, which must be an editing mistake.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.13"
msgid "udako vuccati."
msgstr "what lives in water is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_836
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.14"
msgid "Maṃsaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Meat:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.15"
msgid "yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "the meat of those animals whose meat is allowable."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_837
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.16"
msgid "Khīraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Milk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.17"
msgid "gokhīraṃ vā ajikākhīraṃ vā mahiṃsakhīraṃ vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ khīraṃ."
msgstr "milk from cows, milk from goats, milk from buffaloes, or milk from whatever animal whose meat is allowable."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_838
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.18"
msgid "Dadhi nāma"
msgstr "Curd:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.19"
msgid "tesaññeva dadhi."
msgstr "curd from those same animals."

#. HTML: </span></p></div><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, pts-vp-pli4.89, pts-vp-en.2.343, ms2V_839
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.20"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.21"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.22"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.23"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.24"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_840
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.25"
msgid "Evarūpāni paṇītabhojanānīti"
msgstr "Any of these kinds of fine foods:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.26"
msgid "tathārūpāni paṇītabhojanāni."
msgstr "such kinds of fine foods."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_841
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.27"
msgid "Agilāno nāma"
msgstr "Not sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.28"
msgid "yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni phāsu hoti."
msgstr "one who is comfortable without fine foods."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms2V_842
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.29"
msgid "Gilāno nāma"
msgstr "Sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.30"
msgid "yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "one who is not comfortable without fine foods."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. VAR: viññāpeti, payoge → payoge payoge (pts1, mr)
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_843
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.31"
msgid "Agilāno attano atthāya viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "If he is not sick, then for the act of asking for himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.32"
msgid "Paṭilābhena “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "When he receives it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.1.33"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc21, pts-cs-bu-pc39.3.2, ms2V_844
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.1"
msgid "Agilāno agilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, and he does not perceive himself as sick, and he eats fine foods after asking for them for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.2"
msgid "Agilāno vematiko paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he eats fine foods after asking for them for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.3"
msgid "Agilāno gilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he eats fine foods after asking for them for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_845
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.4"
msgid "Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is sick, but he does not perceive himself as sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.5"
msgid "Gilāno vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is sick, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.2.6"
msgid "Gilāno gilānasaññī anāpatti."
msgstr "If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-pc39.3.3, ms2V_846
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.2"
msgid "gilānassa,"
msgstr "if he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.3"
msgid "gilāno hutvā viññāpetvā agilāno bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he asked for it when he was sick, but eats it when he is no longer sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.4"
msgid "gilānassa sesakaṃ bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the leftovers from one who is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.5"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.6"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.7"
msgid "attano,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.8"
msgid "dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc24, ms2V_847
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:3.3.11"
msgid "Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on fine foods, is finished."
